---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 452
  - Title: Laws
    Location: XI 933 D
By: Plato
Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Subversion-The Wrathful Side=Sorcery
---
The sort of man who injures others by magic knots, or enchantments, or
incantations, or any of the like practices, if he be a prophet or
diviner, let him die.
